# OpenMultiTrack context

FOSS Android multitrack recorder + virtual soundcheck for Behringer/Midas USB mixers. GPLv3-or-later, F-Droid target.

## Read before non-trivial work

1. [docs/AGENTS.md](../../docs/AGENTS.md) — mission, pitfalls, module map
2. [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md) — documentation index
3. [docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md](../../docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md) — what is done vs missing

## Modules (7)

`app` · `domain` · `usb-audio` · `audio-engine` · `session-io` · `mixer-behringer` · `remote-server`

Dependency rule: `app` → libraries; `domain` has **no** Android imports.

## Submodule required

```bash
git submodule update --init --recursive
```

Oboe lives in `third_party/oboe`.

## Do not assume outdated docs

- `remote-server` **exists** (NanoHTTPD LAN sync — not Ktor browser UI)
- Per-channel WAV sessions + DAW UI are shipped
- [control-api.md](../../docs/control-api.md) is superseded by [remote-control.md](../../docs/remote-control.md)
